NTE|3||FEU. The D-dimer concentration in normal non-pregnant
NTE|4||individuals will be less than 650 ng/mL FEU, based on an

NTE|8||(DVT) - the acute phase of clot formation and in pulmonary
NTE|9||embolism (PE)-the fibronolytic stage.  Trauma, recent
NTE|10||surgery, cancer, sepsis, DIC, rheumatoid arthritis or
NTE|11||complications of pregnancy can non-specifically elevate
NTE|12||the D-dimer above the upper limit of "normal".

OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|33|  The Pap smear is a screening test for the detection of cervical cancer||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|34|  and its precursor lesions.  False positive and false negative results||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|35|  can occur. The test should be performed at regular intervals, and||||||F
OBX||TX|APRESULT^.|36|  positive results should be confirmed before definitive therapy.||||||F
